<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1858,2004]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
Five species from 
<collectingCountry box="[366,522,1858,1884]" name="New Zealand" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
are recognized in this genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Mound" box="[870,1153,1858,1884]" pageId="4" pageNumber="68" refString="Mound, L. A. &amp; Walker, A. K. (1986) Tubulifera (Insecta: Thysanoptera). Fauna of New Zealand, 10, 1 - 140." type="journal article" year="1986">
Mound &amp; Walker, 
<number box="[1091,1153,1858,1884]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" value="1986.0">1986</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), together with two species from 
<collectingCountry box="[267,418,1898,1924]" name="South Africa" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">South Africa</collectingCountry>
and one from 
<collectingCountry box="[588,746,1898,1924]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
. These eight species exhibit considerable differences in the length of the tube, but they are essentially similar in the form of the head, thorax and antennae. The 
<collectingCountry name="New Zealand" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
species that is recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[596,703,1978,2004]" name="Australia" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">Australia</collectingCountry>
has the tube shorter than any other member of the genus.
</paragraph>
